  "text": "Incentives: Volunteers who run nodes are rewarded with publicity and possibly better anonymity [CITATION_1] . More nodes means increased scalability, and more users can mean more anonymity. We need to continue examining the incentive structures for participating in Tor. Further, we need to explore more approaches to limiting abuse, and understand why most people don't bother using privacy systems.",
